						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the central shrine in the Gōmuktīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I) Year 38: 945 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that when the King worshipped the deity at Tiruvāvaḍutuṟai in Śāttaṉūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Tiraimūr-nāḍu, on seeing that the shrine was being constructed in stone he donated five hundred <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> to cover the shrine from <hi rend="italic">Kuḍappaḍai</hi> upwards, in gold. </p>						

						</summary>
